{
  "text": "Let K \u03c9 , \u03c9 \u2208 \u2126, be a measurable family of compact subsets of T d satisfying (1.10) with f (\u03c9) the same as in the Introduction. Set K = {(x, \u03c9) : x \u2208 K \u03c9 }. Then we have the setup of \"random bundle maps\" from [CITATION_1] , and can speak about the relativized topological entropy h (r) top (\u03c4, K) of the skew product transformation \u03c4 restricted to the \u03c4 -invariant set K.",
